##                SNP Chromosome Position     P.value       maf nobs
## 1 EH23b.chr1_48433          1    48433 0.007848276 0.4907407  270
## 2 EH23b.chr1_54381          1    54381 0.732150539 0.2833333  270
## 3 EH23b.chr1_61575          1    61575 0.009882854 0.4962963  270
if(length(grep("POS", names(gwas))) == 0){
  #is.na(gwas$POS) <- TRUE
  #gwas$POS <- gwas$Pos
  gwas$POS <- gwas$Position
  for(i in 2:nrow(nucs)){
#      gwas$POS[ gwas$Chr == nucs$Id[i] ] <- gwas$Pos[ gwas$Chr == nucs$Id[i] ] + sum( nucs$Length[1:(i - 1)] )
      gwas$POS[ gwas$Chr == nucs$chrom_num[i] ] <- gwas$Pos[ gwas$Chr == nucs$chrom_num[i] ] + sum( nucs$Length[1:(i - 1)] )
  }
}
gwas$log_pvalue <- -log10(gwas$P.value)
gwas$alpha <- gwas$log_pvalue / max(gwas$log_pvalue)
gwas$alpha <- round(gwas$alpha, digits = 2)
#gwas[1:3, ]

gwas$chrom_num <- sub(".+\\chr", "", gwas$Chr)
gwas$chrom_num[ gwas$chrom_num == "X" ] <- 10
gwas$chrom_num[ gwas$chrom_num == "Y" ] <- 11
gwas$chrom_num <- as.numeric( gwas$chrom_num )

my_pal <- c("#420A6866", "#D94D3D66", "#FCAF1366", "#BF395266", 
            "#81206C66", "#62146E66", "#ED692566", "#A12A6366", 
            "#F98B0B66", "#F6D64566"
)
my_pal <- substr(start = 1, stop = 7, my_pal)
gwas$col <- my_pal[gwas$chrom_num]


p <- ggplot( data = gwas, mapping = aes( x = POS, y = log_pvalue) )

my_locus <- "4_68382150"
# my_locus <- "4_36256098"
# my_locus <- "7_290913"

# my_locus <- "X_44482355"

#my_alleles <- paste(getREF(vcf)[my_locus == chr_pos], getALT(vcf)[my_locus == chr_pos], sep = "/")
my_alleles <- paste( "0 = ", getREF(vcf)[my_locus == chr_pos], "; 1 = ", getALT(vcf)[my_locus == chr_pos], sep = "")

my_dat <- data.frame(
  #Varin_Total = pheno$Varin_Total,
  Varin_Total = pheno$Total,
  gt = gt2[my_locus, ],
  pcol = "#00000044"
)
#my_dat$pcol[ my_dat$gt == 2 ] <- "#B22222"

#lm1 <- lm( Varin_Total ~ gt, data = my_dat )
lm1 <- lm( Varin_Total ~ gt, data = my_dat[ my_dat$gt != 2, ] )
lm11 <- lm( Varin_Total ~ gt + I(gt^2), data = my_dat )

my_vals <- data.frame(
  x = seq(0, 2, length.out=10)
)
my_vals$y <- lm11$coefficients[1] + my_vals$x * lm11$coefficients[2] + my_vals$x^2 * lm11$coefficients[3]

#my_dat$gt <- as.factor(my_dat$gt)
my_dat$gt2 <- as.factor(my_dat$gt)
lm12 <- lm( Varin_Total ~ gt2, data = my_dat )
#my_dat$gt <- as.numeric(my_dat$gt)

Supplemental Figure 25. Varin (pentyl) cannabinoid ratio GWAS A) Significant GWA hits, using the BLINK model and normalized varin cannabinoid ratio data. B) Histogram of propyl:pentyl cannabinoid ratios for the F2 population (left), and arcsinh transformed propyl:pentyl cannabinoid ratios (right).

Supplemental Figure 25. Genomic markers associated with varin (pentyl) cannabinoid production. A) Genome wide association study, using the BLINK model from GAPIT (PCA.total = 6) to test for an association between genomic markers and varin cannabinoid ratio data. Positions plotted with a high elevation have significant associations with the varin production phenotype. B) Distribution of propyl:pentyl cannabinoid ratios for the F2 population. C) Varin content associated with a marker at chromosome 4, position 67,626,398. D) Varin content associated with a marker at chromosome 7, position 290,840. Note the bimodality in the phenotype data when the marker at chromosome 4, position 67,626,398 is not included.

#gff[1:3, 1:8]
mRNA <- gff[ gff[ ,3] == "mRNA" , ]
#mRNA[1:3,]
mRNA[,10] <- unlist(lapply(strsplit(mRNA[, 9], split = ";"), function(x){ grep("eggnog_free_text_desc=", x, value = TRUE) }))
mRNA[,10] <- sub("eggnog_free_text_desc=", "", mRNA[,10])
mRNA[,11] <- unlist(lapply(strsplit(mRNA[, 9], split = ";"), function(x){ grep("^ID=", x, value = TRUE) }))
mRNA[,11] <- sub("^ID=", "", mRNA[,11])

for(i in 1:4){
  my_chrom <- mRNA[ mRNA[, 1] == gwas_top$Chr[i], ]
  if( any(i == c(2, 3)) ){
    my_buffer <- 1e5
  } else {
    my_buffer <- my_buf
  }
  my_win <- my_chrom[ my_chrom[, 4] >= gwas_top$Pos[i] - my_buffer & my_chrom[, 5] <= gwas_top$Pos[i] + my_buffer, ]
  
  print(knitr::kable(gwas_top[i, c(2:6, 8, 10)], row.names = FALSE, digits=3, format.args = list(big.mark=",")))
  print(knitr::kable(my_win[, c(1,4, 10)], row.names = FALSE))
}
